import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    grouped_data = data.groupby('origin')['count'].sum().reset_index()
    ax = grouped_data.plot.bar(x='origin', y='count', legend=False)
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of flight counts between different origins?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data.groupby('destination')['count'].sum().plot(kind='bar')
    plt.xlabel('Destination')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight counts between different destinations?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
